(70 Hun, 599.) DEYOE v. WOODWORTH et al. (Supreme Court, General Term, Third Department. July 8, 1893.) Appeal from circuit court, Saratoga county. Action by Daniel H. Deyoe against Herbert J. Woodworth and others. From a judgment of nonsuit, plaintiff appeals. Affirmed.

Argued before MAYHAM, P. J., and PUTNAM and HERRICK, JJ.

Gayley, Baucus & Fleming, (Edgar T. Brackett, of counsel,) for appellant. T. F. Hamilton, for respondents. HERRICK, J.

This is a companion case to Deyoe v. Ewen, 24 N. Y. Supp. 372, (decided at this term of the court,) and the questions involved are the same. The judgment appealed from is affirmed, with costs. All concur.
